                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G Economic and Financial Problems/21:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hull</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-18T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 18, 1933—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. Your 67, December 18, 5 p.m. I have consulted the President who approves of
                    Dr. Puig’s resolution as it stands. With regard to Mr. Braden’s statement the
                    President suggests that we may not be in a position to discuss definite plans at
                    the Santiago Conference if held within the next few months—certainly not within
                    6 months at least.</p>
                <p>Assume Mr. Braden has checked accuracy of statement regarding “greatly increased
                    exports” of principal countries of South America to the United States since
                    June.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
